1
00:00:39,572 --> 00:00:42,268
We're not a threat, We're salvation,

2
00:00:42,509 --> 00:00:44,568
The world will have to deal with us.

3
00:00:45,111 --> 00:00:47,011
Previously on The 4400:

4
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:48,704
Lily, are you all right?

5
00:00:49,783 --> 00:00:51,580
- Where's my wife?
- What are you talking about?

6
00:00:51,751 --> 00:00:55,847
Mr. Tyler, when your wife fainted this
morning, she was a young woman.

7
00:00:56,022 --> 00:00:57,956
When she woke up
less than a minute later,

8
00:00:58,124 --> 00:01:00,490
she was 50 years older?

9
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:01,888
Are you my mother?

10
00:01:03,163 --> 00:01:04,790
Richard, I'm dying.

11
00:01:04,964 --> 00:01:07,228
I understand there was
an incident this morning.

12
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,231
You attempted to harm yourself.

13
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:11,035
You had no right to do that!

14
00:01:11,204 --> 00:01:14,264
Don't you understand who you are?
What you're here to do?

15
00:01:14,441 --> 00:01:18,104
I'm injecting myself with a modified
version of the promicin serum.

16
00:01:18,278 --> 00:01:22,078
I will have taught my body
how to produce promicin.

17
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:27,447
And then I will be the first non-returnee
to develop 4400 abilities.

18
00:01:27,620 --> 00:01:29,349
That was T.J. Kim
running from the courthouse.

19
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:32,616
When she hit, T.J. drove every man
in the building into a homicidal rage.

20
00:01:32,792 --> 00:01:34,384
Ever since we took them
off the inhibitor,

21
00:01:34,561 --> 00:01:36,085
they're either developing
new abilities

22
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:38,196
or they're refining the ones
that they've got.

23
00:01:38,364 --> 00:01:39,831
So they are getting more dangerous.

24
00:01:39,999 --> 00:01:42,092
You saved my life. I owe you.

25
00:01:43,369 --> 00:01:44,529
You sold us out.

26
00:01:44,704 --> 00:01:47,298
I don't guess we'll be seeing her
in court anytime soon.

27
00:01:47,474 --> 00:01:48,907
This is a message
from the Nova Group,

28
00:01:49,075 --> 00:01:51,839
We are the defensive Wing
of the 4400,

29
00:01:52,011 --> 00:01:53,706
Today, the World has seen
What happens

30
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,643
to those Who try to harm us,

31
00:01:55,815 --> 00:01:58,010
A neW era daWns,

32
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,365
Hi.

33
00:02:19,205 --> 00:02:21,833
I'll need your auxiliary rounds as well,
Agent Baldwin.

34
00:02:22,675 --> 00:02:24,040
Oh, yeah.

35
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:27,043
Of course. I forgot again.

36
00:02:27,213 --> 00:02:29,374
- Thanks. You can go in.
- Great.

37
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,548
Hi, T.J.

38
00:02:44,564 --> 00:02:46,191
What do you want?

39
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,800
Dr. Burkhoff?

40
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:51,736
I have your prescriptions.

41
00:02:52,939 --> 00:02:54,634
Hello?

42
00:02:55,241 --> 00:02:56,708
Say something if you're here.

43
00:02:56,876 --> 00:02:59,071
No, don't.

44
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:01,074
Please.

45
00:03:03,082 --> 00:03:04,549
I've been having migraines.

46
00:03:05,985 --> 00:03:07,384
How severe?

47
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,250
Bad enough.

48
00:03:10,423 --> 00:03:11,947
Don't worry. They're just headaches.

49
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:13,717
I've been getting them for years.

50
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:22,226
Seven forty-five.

51
00:03:22,402 --> 00:03:25,337
You're just in time
for my wake-up call.

52
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:30,069
These promicin shots,
how many a day are you up to now?

53
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:33,871
Six.

54
00:03:34,981 --> 00:03:36,414
You've doubled your dosage?

55
00:03:37,584 --> 00:03:39,882
I thought you weren't gonna do that
without talking to me.

56
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:41,418
We're talking now.

57
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:46,355
Look, I'm training my body
to produce a new neurotransmitter.

58
00:03:46,526 --> 00:03:48,994
And I guarantee you,
I'm not the only one trying.

59
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:53,957
The moment the first 4400
manifested an ability,

60
00:03:54,133 --> 00:03:56,328
an arms race began.

61
00:03:56,603 --> 00:03:59,868
Someone is going to produce
a promicin serum

62
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:03,702
that will cause non-4400s
to develop extraordinary abilities.

63
00:04:03,876 --> 00:04:05,070
It will happen.

64
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:06,872
And the only questions are:

65
00:04:07,046 --> 00:04:10,641
who's going to do it?
And who's going to control it?

66
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:14,981
Hopefully, someone with a highly
developed sense of responsibility.

67
00:04:15,388 --> 00:04:16,582
And some judgment.

68
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:17,916
Let me ask you,

69
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:20,719
do you meet many people like that
in your day-to-day affairs?

70
00:04:20,893 --> 00:04:22,952
Do a lot of them
hold high-ranking government posts

71
00:04:23,129 --> 00:04:26,621
or sit on the board
of giant pharmaceutical companies?

72
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:30,929
Dr. Burkhoff, I knew
that you had some personality quirks,

73
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,265
but I never pegged you for a cynic.

74
00:04:36,843 --> 00:04:40,506
I can't afford to have a charitable view
of human nature.

75
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,272
There's too much at stake here.

76
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:45,611
If these experiments
cost me some headaches,

77
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:47,275
some sores,

78
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:49,853
I'd say that's a price worth paying.

79
00:04:50,556 --> 00:04:52,217
Wouldn't you?

80
00:04:53,226 --> 00:04:55,319
I'm here, right?

81
00:05:53,986 --> 00:05:55,510
Holy mother!

82
00:06:02,628 --> 00:06:04,619
Why are we doing this?

83
00:06:04,797 --> 00:06:06,697
Everything I'm telling you,
it's all in my file.

84
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,629
You know it already.

85
00:06:08,801 --> 00:06:10,325
Relax, T.J.

86
00:06:10,503 --> 00:06:11,902
I just think it's important we review

87
00:06:12,071 --> 00:06:13,766
everything you told
the government so far.

88
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:16,272
- Have we?
- Yes.

89
00:06:16,442 --> 00:06:19,536
I keep telling you, yes.
That's everything I know.

90
00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:22,637
Okay.

91
00:06:22,815 --> 00:06:24,407
Thanks for your cooperation.

92
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:30,487
We're just trying
to consolidate information.

93
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:34,592
You'd be amazed how hard
that can be in a bureaucracy.

94
00:06:34,861 --> 00:06:39,491
Yeah, well, I hope you don't expect
me to say, "You're welcome."

95
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:42,829
What are you doing?

96
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,596
What, this?

97
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:49,064
It's nothing.
I'm just wrapping up the interview.

98
00:08:15,027 --> 00:08:16,654
Get geared up.
We're leaving in two minutes.

99
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,763
What for? What's going on?

100
00:08:19,031 --> 00:08:21,465
Your partner registered
to see T.J. Kim this morning.

101
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:23,431
When Tom left the interview room,
T.J. was dead.

102
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:25,468
- What?
- Two gunshot wounds to the head.

103
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:28,471
Apparently, Tom snuck a small firearm
into the interrogation room.

104
00:08:28,641 --> 00:08:30,939
By the time the guard went in
and found T.J.'s body,

105
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,668
Tom had already left the building.

106
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:34,710
- I'm going to pick him up now.
- Oh, wait, wait.

107
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:37,873
This is Tom we're talking about, here.
There's gotta be some explanation.

108
00:08:38,050 --> 00:08:40,211
Now, maybe T.J.
used her ability on him.

109
00:08:40,386 --> 00:08:43,116
No, she had concentrated promicin
inhibitor pumping through her veins.

110
00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:45,450
We tried to contact Tom,
but he hasn't been picking up.

111
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:47,616
We need to get him in
and figure out what happened.

112
00:08:47,793 --> 00:08:50,591
Okay, well just let me talk to him first.
He trusts me.

113
00:08:50,763 --> 00:08:53,288
Look, this is Tom.

114
00:08:53,466 --> 00:08:55,832
Come on, we owe him that much.

115
00:08:57,336 --> 00:08:59,099
Yeah, okay.

116
00:09:03,576 --> 00:09:06,807
I wasn't trying to drown myself.

117
00:09:07,146 --> 00:09:08,408
I don't even know if I could.

118
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:10,079
Okay.

119
00:09:10,249 --> 00:09:13,707
Isabelle, I just thought that after
everything that happened with Lily--

120
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:16,377
Shawn, this has nothing to do
with my mother.

121
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:21,724
I was teaching myself to swim.

122
00:09:23,596 --> 00:09:25,359
In your clothes?

123
00:09:25,531 --> 00:09:27,965
I never wore a bathing suit before.

124
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:30,034
I didn't know what to get.

125
00:09:31,003 --> 00:09:32,971
And I'm too old to ask for help.

126
00:09:33,139 --> 00:09:35,198
It's embarrassing
not knowing how to swim.

127
00:09:35,374 --> 00:09:38,241
Everybody's got to learn sometime,
lsabelle.

128
00:09:38,878 --> 00:09:40,778
I learned when I was a kid.

129
00:09:40,947 --> 00:09:42,471
But I never was a kid.

130
00:09:42,648 --> 00:09:45,014
That's why I never learned
how to swim or how to drive.

131
00:09:45,184 --> 00:09:47,550
Or ever went out on a date.

132
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:51,315
I keep reading
about all these rites of passage.

133
00:09:51,490 --> 00:09:54,118
Like stuff everyone goes through
before they grow up, yeah?

134
00:09:54,293 --> 00:09:56,193
Yeah, but I am grown up.

135
00:09:56,362 --> 00:09:58,626
And I missed out on all of it.

136
00:09:59,498 --> 00:10:00,795
It's not fair.

137
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:05,194
- I've got to catch up, so I made a list.
- A list?

138
00:10:05,371 --> 00:10:07,396
That's pretty organized.

139
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:11,338
Well, lsabelle,
there is a pool at the Center.

140
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:13,444
I could probably teach you
the basics.

141
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,046
Really?

142
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,346
Thanks, Shawn.

143
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,667
Dad?

144
00:10:36,669 --> 00:10:38,762
How old were you
when you learned how to swim?

145
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:44,203
Oh, about 1 1, I guess.

146
00:10:45,378 --> 00:10:47,608
Why? You want me to teach you?

147
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:50,248
That's okay. Shawn said he'd do it.

148
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:52,875
Oh, he did, did he?

149
00:10:53,419 --> 00:10:54,681
Well,

150
00:10:54,854 --> 00:10:57,186
make sure he doesn't throw you
in the deep end right away.

151
00:10:57,356 --> 00:11:00,086
That's what my grandmother
did to me.

152
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:03,360
Look, lsabelle.
I'm gonna be gone overnight.

153
00:11:03,529 --> 00:11:06,692
- If you need anything, go see Shawn.
- Where are you going?

154
00:11:08,768 --> 00:11:10,759
I'm gonna take your mother home.

155
00:11:11,303 --> 00:11:13,066
I'm putting her to rest.

156
00:11:13,572 --> 00:11:15,062
Well, can I come with you?

157
00:11:17,243 --> 00:11:18,232
I don't think so.

158
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:20,876
I'm flying

159
00:11:22,248 --> 00:11:24,011
and to tell you the truth,

160
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:27,050
I don't think you're ready to be away
from the Center yet.

161
00:11:28,754 --> 00:11:32,349
You want to be alone with her
when you say goodbye, don't you?

162
00:11:36,762 --> 00:11:38,992
Yeah. I guess I do.

163
00:12:13,966 --> 00:12:15,593
- Tom.
- Oh, God!

164
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:19,569
You scared the hell out of me, Diana.
What are you doing here?

165
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:23,040
Why is your gun out?
What the hell is going on?

166
00:12:23,209 --> 00:12:25,268
Jarvis is on her way over,
she's got everyone with her.

167
00:12:25,444 --> 00:12:26,877
You need to come in.

168
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:30,579
- Why? What are you talking about?
- You shot T.J. Kim this morning.

169
00:12:31,383 --> 00:12:32,714
- What?
- You don't remember?

170
00:12:32,885 --> 00:12:34,352
Don't remember?
I didn't shoot anybody.

171
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:37,011
- I've been here all morning.
- Can someone confirm that?

172
00:12:38,457 --> 00:12:42,018
No, no, I was supposed to have
a conference call with Kyle's attorneys.

173
00:12:42,194 --> 00:12:43,718
They cancelled, though.

174
00:12:44,196 --> 00:12:46,255
Look, I took a half a personal day,
Diana.

175
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:49,026
I went jogging. I wasn't at work.

176
00:12:49,201 --> 00:12:52,728
You gotta stop saying that because
two dozen people saw you there.

177
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:55,806
Look, I don't know
what's going on. I--

178
00:12:56,408 --> 00:12:58,842
Maybe you're blacking out
like Kyle did.

179
00:12:59,011 --> 00:13:02,139
Maybe it's something else.
Maybe it's like some 4400 ability.

180
00:13:02,314 --> 00:13:05,511
I mean, I don't know,
but you gotta come in.

181
00:13:05,851 --> 00:13:07,341
And what happens if I do?

182
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:10,045
- I get arrested for murder?
- You know, we'll figure it out, okay?

183
00:13:10,222 --> 00:13:12,884
Everyone wants to help you.
You just have to come in.

184
00:13:16,695 --> 00:13:19,960
- You mind if I get dressed first?
- Oh, sure.

185
00:13:24,403 --> 00:13:26,564
Are you sure you remember everything
you did this morning?

186
00:13:26,739 --> 00:13:29,435
Like there's no time gaps
or anything?

187
00:13:29,608 --> 00:13:31,542
You didn't take a nap?

188
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,575
Because, Tom...

189
00:13:35,014 --> 00:13:36,606
Tom?

190
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:42,578
Damn it!

191
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:50,659
Yeah, hi, it's me. He got away.

192
00:13:52,398 --> 00:13:55,561
I don't know how.
They only sent one agent after him.

193
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:58,669
Look, sorry. He got away.

194
00:13:58,971 --> 00:14:02,930
What? No way. He's an NTAC agent.
He'll be expecting that.

195
00:14:03,909 --> 00:14:05,274
Okay.

196
00:14:05,878 --> 00:14:07,675
You're right. This has to happen.

197
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:09,314
I'll do it.

198
00:14:09,982 --> 00:14:11,813
I was letting him get dressed.

199
00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:14,418
I didn't think he would jump
from a second story window.

200
00:14:14,587 --> 00:14:17,112
Well, obviously you underestimated
your partner's resolve.

201
00:14:17,289 --> 00:14:19,621
- Does he still seem blameless to you?
- I don't know.

202
00:14:19,792 --> 00:14:22,659
Look, it was a really bad call
and I take full responsibility.

203
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,489
I've alerted local law enforcement,
the FBl.

204
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:26,661
I've told them that Tom
is wanted for questioning

205
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:29,392
in connection with a murder.
He's a fugitive now.

206
00:14:29,568 --> 00:14:31,866
Oh, don't give me that look, Diana.
I had no choice.

207
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:35,071
Sorry.

208
00:14:35,241 --> 00:14:36,469
- It's Tom.
- Yeah.

209
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:38,471
Tom.

210
00:14:38,644 --> 00:14:40,009
I'm sorry I ran out on you,

211
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:42,511
- Where are you?
- I didn't kill T.J. I didn't kill anyone.

212
00:14:42,681 --> 00:14:45,479
I believe you. But you have to come in,
we can figure out what's going on.

213
00:14:45,651 --> 00:14:48,142
- No, I'm not going to jail,
- No one's gonna put you in prison.

214
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,787
They did it to my son, Diana,

215
00:14:50,422 --> 00:14:53,084
Was it really him that pulled the trigger
the day Jordan Collier died?

216
00:14:53,259 --> 00:14:55,386
No, it wasn't, was it?
It was that thing inside of him.

217
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:57,791
- And where's Kyle? He's incarcerated.
- You're a fugitive,

218
00:14:57,963 --> 00:15:00,363
Every police department
in Washington is looking for you.

219
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:02,625
NoW, some local cop
Wants to be a hero, spots you,

220
00:15:02,801 --> 00:15:04,098
you know how these things can end.

221
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:06,397
No, it's gonna end with me
proving I didn't do this.

222
00:15:07,306 --> 00:15:08,898
Look, dig around, Diana,

223
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:10,905
There's got to be some evidence
that'll clear me.

224
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:14,409
Just help me find it.

225
00:15:16,615 --> 00:15:18,207
Did he give you a location?

226
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:29,184
Marco, help me out here.

227
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:32,495
If you were trying to prove
that your partner didn't commit a crime

228
00:15:32,665 --> 00:15:35,293
that the whole world thinks he did,

229
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:37,298
where would you start?

230
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:42,006
Well, I guess I'd start by pretending
that my partner wasn't involved.

231
00:15:43,642 --> 00:15:46,202
Okay, just think of it
like any other case.

232
00:15:46,378 --> 00:15:48,039
What's the first thing you do
when you start?

233
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:49,680
Well, look at the evidence.

234
00:15:50,082 --> 00:15:53,313
I mean, there's a dead body.
There's the gun that Tom left behind.

235
00:15:53,485 --> 00:15:55,510
And there's a bunch of people
that saw him here.

236
00:15:57,289 --> 00:16:00,349
Well, they've got security cameras
down in the detention ward, right?

237
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:02,922
You're serious?

238
00:16:03,095 --> 00:16:05,290
You're really asking me
for all that footage?

239
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,591
Of course I'm serious.
Is that a problem?

240
00:16:07,766 --> 00:16:09,324
Well, it's just...

241
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:13,263
I gave all the tapes to him,
like, an hour ago.

242
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:17,667
What are you talking about?
I haven't been up here all day.

243
00:16:18,377 --> 00:16:19,844
What is this, a joke?

244
00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:23,074
Marco, come on.
You were just here.

245
00:16:23,248 --> 00:16:25,739
You signed for all the footage
from the detention ward.

246
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:32,855
- This isn't so hard.
- That's because I haven't let go yet.

247
00:16:33,025 --> 00:16:34,890
All right, I'm gonna move my hands.
