00:30:47,478 --> 00:30:49,742
I lost it. I must have lost it
while I was running around.

487
00:30:49,914 --> 00:30:53,714
Come on, it's me, Tom, Alana.
I gave you the password.

488
00:31:00,658 --> 00:31:03,627
Please don't make me.
I don't have anything against you.

489
00:31:08,099 --> 00:31:10,897
Tom, it says it's your house.

490
00:31:11,436 --> 00:31:14,428
- Alana?
- I Wrote a letter on your computer,

491
00:31:14,606 --> 00:31:16,073
You need to come sign it.

492
00:31:16,608 --> 00:31:18,803
- Boyd?
- It's a confession,

493
00:31:18,977 --> 00:31:20,672
It says you cracked under the strain

494
00:31:20,845 --> 00:31:23,279
of the murder charges
against your son.

495
00:31:23,448 --> 00:31:26,144
You shot T.J.
and now you can't live with it.

496
00:31:26,317 --> 00:31:29,150
- So you decided to kill yourself.
- Where is Alana? What did you do?

497
00:31:30,021 --> 00:31:32,080
It's my get-out-of-jail-free card.

498
00:31:32,257 --> 00:31:34,885
See, you're the only one
who can identify me.

499
00:31:35,059 --> 00:31:37,459
Everyone else,
they've just been seeing double.

500
00:31:37,629 --> 00:31:40,723
- They'll sound crazy.
- I'm not signing a suicide note, Boyd,

501
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:43,493
- Put Alana on the phone.
- Oh, you'll sign,

502
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:45,101
Because either I shoot you

503
00:31:46,437 --> 00:31:48,098
or I shoot her.

504
00:31:48,273 --> 00:31:50,036
It's a trade.

505
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:54,879
Your life for hers.

506
00:32:00,218 --> 00:32:01,412
You know what?

507
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:04,020
I don't think I can let you do this, Tom.
We need to call Jarvis.

508
00:32:04,188 --> 00:32:06,748
We need to block off the street.
We need to surround your house.

509
00:32:06,925 --> 00:32:09,792
- He has Alana.
- Tom, he wants to kill you.

510
00:32:09,961 --> 00:32:12,395
The least we can do
is make it a little bit difficult for him.

511
00:32:12,563 --> 00:32:14,497
If it was Maia in there,

512
00:32:14,666 --> 00:32:16,725
would you call Jarvis?

513
00:32:26,010 --> 00:32:27,671
Do you like it?

514
00:32:28,413 --> 00:32:30,210
Why did you bring this to me?

515
00:32:30,381 --> 00:32:32,042
You're a young woman.

516
00:32:32,216 --> 00:32:33,979
A young woman
should have a nice dress.

517
00:32:35,486 --> 00:32:38,387
This is gonna look good on you.
See for yourself.

518
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:49,693
Thank you.

519
00:32:51,169 --> 00:32:54,138
I see you've been
spending a lot of time with Shawn.

520
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:55,772
So?

521
00:32:56,107 --> 00:32:57,802
Well, I think it's wonderful.

522
00:32:57,976 --> 00:32:59,773
Shawn's a very isolated young man.

523
00:32:59,944 --> 00:33:03,471
He doesn't get to spend much time
around people his own age.

524
00:33:05,216 --> 00:33:06,774
I think

525
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:09,912
you should get
as close to him as you can.

526
00:33:13,624 --> 00:33:15,114
Matthew?

527
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:19,061
Shawn's nice.

528
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:20,822
And what I'm doing with him
is not for you

529
00:33:20,999 --> 00:33:23,126
and it's not because
I'm trying to use him.

530
00:33:23,768 --> 00:33:25,633
Of course not.

531
00:33:25,803 --> 00:33:28,101
But eventually, lsabelle,

532
00:33:28,272 --> 00:33:29,967
you and Shawn
are gonna be on opposite sides

533
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:32,575
of a very large ideological divide.

534
00:33:33,911 --> 00:33:36,778
So enjoy your friendship.

535
00:33:36,948 --> 00:33:38,745
But don't let your emotions
run too deep.

536
00:33:39,384 --> 00:33:41,352
If you do,

537
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:43,180
it'll make things more difficult later.

538
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:48,248
- What things?
- You'll know.

539
00:33:51,229 --> 00:33:52,856
It doesn't match your eyes.

540
00:33:53,031 --> 00:33:55,261
You should take care of that.

541
00:34:20,691 --> 00:34:22,818
You were a beautiful woman.

542
00:34:25,329 --> 00:34:26,956
Both of you.

543
00:34:31,369 --> 00:34:33,667
You looked exactly alike.

544
00:34:35,273 --> 00:34:37,673
I never could figure out why.

545
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:42,769
But one way or the other,
I've had a Lily in my life

546
00:34:42,947 --> 00:34:44,380
for over 50 years.

547
00:34:48,653 --> 00:34:50,814
That's all gone now.

548
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:54,214
And I don't know what I'm gonna do.

549
00:35:02,233 --> 00:35:05,498
But it makes me feel better
knowing the two of you are together.

550
00:35:06,604 --> 00:35:08,367
Forever.

551
00:35:39,103 --> 00:35:40,968
This is it for you, you know.

552
00:35:41,139 --> 00:35:43,972
I don't know what kind of fairy tale
the Nova Group sold you,

553
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:47,407
but it doesn't matter
what happens to me or Tom.

554
00:35:47,578 --> 00:35:50,376
Your life is over.
They sent you on a suicide mission.

555
00:35:50,548 --> 00:35:52,106
I volunteered.

556
00:35:52,283 --> 00:35:55,480
And I don't think you're in any spot
to be giving me advice.

557
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:58,853
You're a 4400.

558
00:35:59,023 --> 00:36:00,888
You're special.

559
00:36:01,058 --> 00:36:03,026
You're supposed to be
changing things.

560
00:36:04,629 --> 00:36:06,028
Instead you live
with an NTAC agent.

561
00:36:06,197 --> 00:36:08,165
And what are you going to change,
Boyd?

562
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:09,959
You killed a girl.

563
00:36:10,134 --> 00:36:11,897
How does that
make the world better?

564
00:36:12,069 --> 00:36:14,230
T.J. Kim was a soldier.

565
00:36:14,405 --> 00:36:17,841
She would rather have me
put a bullet in her head than betray us.

566
00:36:21,145 --> 00:36:22,737
Everyone talks
about saving the world.

567
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:26,908
Meanwhile, for the past 50 years,
everything's been turning bad.

568
00:36:27,084 --> 00:36:28,711
One disaster after another.

569
00:36:32,356 --> 00:36:36,486
But we're gonna show the world
a new way.

570
00:36:37,061 --> 00:36:39,529
We're gonna take them down
a new path.

571
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:42,798
By force if we have to.

572
00:36:44,168 --> 00:36:45,430
I mean, can't you see?

573
00:36:45,603 --> 00:36:49,130
The real catastrophe
is to sit back and do nothing.

574
00:36:54,845 --> 00:36:56,574
Did you hear that?

575
00:37:20,504 --> 00:37:21,698
Stop it.

576
00:37:25,943 --> 00:37:29,310
- Stop it, both of you. Stop or I'll shoot.
- Nice work, Alana. We got him.

577
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:30,504
Shut up!

578
00:37:30,681 --> 00:37:33,650
- Alana, Death in Venice,
- Yeah, that's the password.

579
00:37:33,818 --> 00:37:36,787
Come on, Alana. Give me the gun.
We'll call NTAC. It's over.

580
00:37:47,865 --> 00:37:50,095
Alana, it's me, Tom.
Ask me a question. Anything--

581
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:53,135
Wait, don't fall for it.
He's probably read my file.

582
00:37:53,304 --> 00:37:55,169
He knows everything about us.
Don't listen to him.

583
00:37:55,339 --> 00:37:56,738
Ask me something about us.

584
00:37:56,907 --> 00:37:59,034
Something only I would know.
Anything about us.

585
00:37:59,210 --> 00:38:00,837
Shut up, both of you.

586
00:38:01,012 --> 00:38:05,346
Baby, I am so proud of you.
Billy would have been proud.

587
00:38:06,884 --> 00:38:09,580
- You know about Billy?
- Yeah.

588
00:38:09,754 --> 00:38:12,689
That was your son.
He died in a car accident.

589
00:38:12,857 --> 00:38:16,190
Alana, he did research.
Anyone could find that out.

590
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:19,193
Give me the gun.
Just give me the gun.

591
00:38:19,363 --> 00:38:20,990
Alana, give me the gun.

592
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:27,202
- No.
- Alana, give me the gun.

593
00:38:28,372 --> 00:38:31,000
- Come on.
- Get down on the ground.

594
00:38:31,776 --> 00:38:35,041
What? No, no.
You've got the wrong one.

595
00:38:35,246 --> 00:38:37,806
- Think about this.
- I said get down.

596
00:38:39,383 --> 00:38:41,351
Hold still, Boyd.

597
00:38:47,258 --> 00:38:49,055
Don't move.

598
00:38:55,299 --> 00:38:56,561
You're just a boy.

599
00:38:58,135 --> 00:38:59,830
I'm a soldier.

600
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:02,529
- And there are more of us every day.
- Let's go, soldier.

601
00:39:13,884 --> 00:39:16,444
Hey, welcome back.

602
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:18,747
- Yeah, thanks.
- Did everything go okay?

603
00:39:18,923 --> 00:39:20,788
Yeah, thank you.

604
00:39:20,958 --> 00:39:23,153
And thank you
for keeping an eye on lsabelle.

605
00:39:23,327 --> 00:39:24,760
Oh, well.

606
00:39:24,929 --> 00:39:27,727
It's not a problem.
I didn't really do much.

607
00:39:28,566 --> 00:39:30,295
Yeah, well, thank you, anyway.

608
00:39:31,102 --> 00:39:32,967
I worry about her.

609
00:39:34,939 --> 00:39:36,429
Well, you don't really need to.

610
00:39:36,607 --> 00:39:38,768
She seems to be getting along
really well.

611
00:39:40,177 --> 00:39:42,236
I'm her father. It's my job.

612
00:39:48,185 --> 00:39:50,483
And it's harder with lsabelle.

613
00:39:51,822 --> 00:39:54,222
People see her, they see a woman.

614
00:39:55,092 --> 00:39:56,582
A beautiful woman.

615
00:39:57,928 --> 00:40:01,261
And they might forget
that inside she's just a little girl.

616
00:40:07,638 --> 00:40:08,969
Still,

617
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:11,904
I'm glad she has you around,

618
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:13,873
to be a friend.

619
00:41:12,703 --> 00:41:14,330
Shawn.

620
00:41:16,106 --> 00:41:18,734
- How'd you get in here?
- I can do stuff, remember?

621
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:22,077
Yeah.

622
00:41:23,347 --> 00:41:25,338
So, what's up? What do you need?

623
00:41:29,186 --> 00:41:31,313
Just one thing.

624
00:41:34,625 --> 00:41:36,422
It's on my list.

625
00:41:46,070 --> 00:41:48,038
First kiss.

626
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:52,668
This isn't smart, lsabelle.

627
00:41:53,744 --> 00:41:55,507
Okay.

